# Agent Instructions

This project is an Intropy **extractor block**: a .NET console job that reads records from an
external system through an inbound connector and publishes each raw record onto a system topic. It is
a complete, runnable integration on its own, and also composes into a larger system via a sibling
SystemHost.

## Project overview

- Framework: .NET 10
- App type: Console job (no web endpoints)
- Runner: `Intropy.Framework.Hosting.TransactionalIntegration.Job.TransactionalIntegrationRunner`
- Block kind: extractor
- App id / component name: `{{ .name }}`
- Reads from: external system `{{ .sourceSystem }}` via the `{{ .connector }}` connector — Dapr
  binding component `binding.{{ .connector }}` (transport chosen at `intropy system create`)
- Publishes: topic `{{ .publishesTopic }}` on pub/sub component `pubsub` (raw source bytes;
  `intropy system create` links a shared Contracts project so every component on the topic agrees
  on the payload)

## The two run modes (one binary, swapped components folder)

The worker always binds to **stable Dapr component names** — `binding.{{ .connector }}` and `pubsub`.
What those names resolve to is decided entirely by which components folder the Dapr sidecar loads
(`--resources-path`):

- **Standalone** (`task run`): `./local/dapr-components/` — `binding.{{ .connector }}` is
  `bindings.localstorage` reading `./local/storage/inbound`, `pubsub` is `pubsub.in-memory`.
- **Under a SystemHost**: the run backend generates a components folder and points the sidecar at it,
  so `binding.{{ .connector }}` becomes the connector's real transport and `pubsub` becomes Redis.
  The code is identical in both; do not hard-code anything that differs between them here.

## Important files

- `Program.cs` — DI wiring and entrypoint: Dapr client, `AddIntropyFramework`,
  `AddTransactionalIntegration`, the source connector `IFileAdapter` (keyed), the `SourceLister`, the
  receive pipeline, and the `TransactionalIntegrationRunner` that runs it.
- `Configuration/Constants.cs` — the stable component names (`pubsub`, `binding.{{ .connector }}`),
  the published topic, the keyed-adapter key, and the context metadata key. These must match on both
  sides of the folder swap.
- `Receive/` — the receive pipeline: `SourceLister` (lists items waiting at the connector) and the
  `Receiver` → `Enqueuer` → `Completer` steps (read bytes → publish onto the topic → remove the
  source item), composed in `ServiceCollectionExtensions`. Idempotency / business-incident routing
  are intentionally omitted from this light scaffold.
- `local/dapr-components/` — the standalone components (`pubsub`, `binding.{{ .connector }}`).
- `Taskfile.yml` — `task build`, `task run`, `task clean`.

## Scaffold record

`.intropy/scaffold.json` carries this component's edge intent in its `topology` section (block kind,
connector, published topic). `intropy system create` reads the records of all sibling components to
generate a wired SystemHost — do not edit the `topology` section by hand; re-scaffold instead.

The folder name, csproj name, and Dapr app-id must all stay `{{ .name }}` — the SystemHost resolves
this project by that convention (`../{{ .name }}/{{ .name }}.csproj`).

## Build and run

`task run` is the canonical run path. It seeds `./local/storage/inbound` with the sample record and
runs the job once under Dapr; the job drains the source (publishing each record onto the topic and
deleting it) and exits.

```bash
task build        # dotnet build
task run          # seed the inbound folder, then dapr run the job once
task clean        # stop the Dapr app and remove ./local/storage
```

## Wiring into a system

From the parent directory that holds all component folders:

```bash
intropy system create -n <system-name>
dotnet run --project <SystemName>.SystemHost -- check
```

## Framework guidance

How-to knowledge for the Intropy framework (pipelines, blocks, endpoints, Dapr components, testing) lives in the Intropy skills collection under `.agents/skills/`. If it is not installed, run `intropy skills collection add --name intropy --ref harbor.intropy.io/skills/index:latest`.
